Dictionary.Phrase:
The driver executes SQL commands according to the Rapid SCADA communication line period. The main DrvDbDataTransfer mode transfers rows from a source database to a target database.
Databases. The Database tab contains two connections: Source Database - the database where SELECT is executed; Target Database - the database where INSERT or UPSERT is executed. If standard fields are not enough, edit the connection string directly. Examples of connection strings are available at https://www.connectionstrings.com.
Import and transfer commands. Disabled commands are skipped by the driver. If only SELECT is specified, the command works in the legacy mode that imports tags from a database into Rapid SCADA. If SELECT and INSERT / UPSERT are specified, the command transfers data Source -> Target. In this mode the tag list is not used for writing to the target database. If tags are configured in the command, they are also updated from the same SELECT result.
SELECT is executed against Source Database. Before execution, SELECT is processed for date and time patterns: {YYYY}, {YY}, {MM}, {DD}, {HH}, {mm}, {ss}. For example, public."{YYYY}{MM}{DD}.Data" becomes public."20260709.Data". Unknown expressions in curly braces are not replaced.
INSERT / UPSERT is executed against Target Database. The query must be parameterized, and parameter names must match SELECT column names or aliases. Example: SELECT occur_time AS AU_DateReport, description AS AU_Message FROM public.event_data WHERE occur_time >= localtimestamp - interval '5 hour 5 minute 10 second' AND occur_time < localtimestamp - interval '5 hour 5 minute';
INSERT INTO dbo.AlarmLog (AU_DateReport, AU_Message) VALUES (@AU_DateReport, @AU_Message);
For periodic polling, use a bounded time window [start, end), not only a >= condition. Otherwise, the same trailing interval is selected again on every polling cycle. Add a unique index or UPSERT in the target database if duplicate protection is required.
Writes and errors. Batch size = 0 writes rows in one transaction. Batch size greater than 0 splits writes into batches of the specified size. Stop on error stops transfer on the first target write error. If Stop on error is disabled, the driver continues writing following rows and logs the number of errors. If SELECT returns 0 rows, INSERT / UPSERT is not executed and the command result is not logged. If rows are read or an error occurs, the log contains the command, source, target, read row count, written row count, and error text.
Legacy tag import mode. If INSERT / UPSERT is empty, SELECT is read from Source Database and the result is converted to Rapid SCADA tags. In column-based mode, the first result row contains several tag values, and column aliases match Name in the tag list. In row-based mode, the query must return TAGNAME and TAGVALUE, where TAGNAME is matched with Name in the tag list. The tag Code must match the Rapid SCADA device tag code. The same rules are used to update tags after Source -> Target transfer.
Export commands. Export commands write Rapid SCADA command values to a database. Use @cmdVal in SQL for the command value and @cmdNum for the command number. String command length is configured in the export command properties. Do not create regular tags at automatically generated command tag addresses.
Export command examples: INSERT INTO DATATABLE_NAME (COLUMN_1, COLUMN_2, COLUMN_3) VALUES ('TAGNAME00001', @cmdVal, GETDATE());
UPDATE DATATABLE_NAME SET COLUMN_2 = @cmdVal WHERE COLUMN_1 = @cmdNum;
MS SQL. Microsoft.Data.SqlClient is used for MS SQL connections. When deploying, choose the package that matches the server platform: win-x64, win-x32, or linux-x64. If an incompatible build is used, the message Microsoft.Data.SqlClient is not supported on this platform may appear. For remote connections, additional options may be required: Persist Security Info=True;Trust Server Certificate=True;
MySQL. If SSL mode has to be specified, use one of the following values: None or Disabled, Preferred or Prefered, Required, VerifyCA, VerifyFull.
Old project conversion. Old DrvDbDataTransfer XML configuration files can be converted by the DrvDbDataTransfer.Converter console utility. Run it without arguments, drag XML files or a configuration directory into the console, and press Enter. The utility creates an output directory near the source files and writes converted project files there.
